title.narrative: Export growth by participating firms relative to sector export growth

comment.narrative: Calculated as the median value of the firm level relative export growth since the year before participating in the project for allparticipating firms. The relative export growth is defined as the difference in percentage points between export growth of the firmand export growth of the sector. Median value of the indicator as opposed to average value is chosen to avoid impact of outliers.Sectoral export data are based on export by chapters as defined by the Statistical Institute of Turkey (TUIK).
